odato|Antonio Diodato}}\n*{{Official website|http://www.diodatomusic.it}} {{in lang|it}}\n\n{{S-start}}\n{{s-ach}}\n{{succession box\n| before=[[Mahmood (singer)|Mahmood]]\n| title= [[Sanremo Music Festival#Winners|Sanremo Music Festival winner]] | years= [[Sanremo Music Festival 2020|2020]]\n| after= Incumbent\n}}\n{{succession box\n| before=Mahmood<br /> with \"[[Soldi]]\"\n| title= [[Italy in the Eurovision Song Contest]]\n| years= [[Eurovision Song Contest 2020|2020]]\n| after= Incumbent\n}}\n{{S-end}}\n\n{{Italy in Eurovision|state=autocollapse}}\n{{Eurovision Song Contest 2020|state=collapsed}}\n{{Authority control}}\n\n[[Category:1981 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:Italian male singer-songwriters]]\n[[Category:Italian singer-songwriters]]\n[[Category:Place of birth missing (living people)]]\n[[Category:21st-century Italian singers]]\n[[Category:21st-century male singers]]\n[[Category:People of Apulian descent]]\n[[Category:Sanremo Music Festival winners]]\n[[Category:Eurovision Song Contest entrants of 2020]]\n[[Category:Italian Eurovision Song Contest entrants]]\n", "text_old": "{{expand language|topic=|langcode=IT|otherarticle=Diodato (cantante)|date=March 2015}}\n{{short description|Italian singer and songwriter}}\n{{Infobox musical artist\n| background       = solo_singer\n| name             = Diodato\n| image            = Rocking with Antonio Diodato (cropped).jpg\n| caption          = Diodato in 2016\n| birth_place      = [[Aosta]], [[Italy]]\n| birth_name       = Antonio Diodato\n| birth_date       = {{Birth date and age|df=y|1981|08|30}}\n| genre            = [[Pop rock]]\n| years_active     = 2007\u2013present\n| occupation       = Singer, songwriter\n}}\n\n'''Antonio Diodato''' (born 30 August 1981), known simply as '''Diodato''', is an Italian singer-songwriter.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.diodatomusic.it/|title=diodatomusic.it &#124; Sito ufficiale di Diodato}}</ref> He won the [[Sanremo Music Festival 2020|70th edition]] of the [[Sanremo Music Festival]] with the song \"[[Fai rumore]]\" and was scheduled to represent [[Italy in the Eurovision Song Contest 2020|Italy]] in the [[Eurovision Song Contest 2020]] held in [[Rotterdam]], the [[Netherlands]]. Unfortunately, his performance will be postponed due to COVID-19 concerns.\n\n==Career==\nHe has released two studio albums, ''E forse sono pazzo'' (LeNarcisse/Goodfellas)<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.rockol.it/recensioni-musicali/album/5600/diodato-e-forse-sono-pazzo|title=\u221a Recensioni &#124; Dischi &#124; Diodato - E Forse Sono Pazzo su Rockol|first=Rockol com|last=s.r.l|website=Rockol}}</ref> and ''A ritrovar bellezza'' (LeNarcisse/[[RCA]]/SonyMusic).<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.radioitalia.it/news/diodato/nuova_uscita/9169_a_ritrovar_bellezza_le_canzoni_degli_anni_sessanta_secondo_diodato.php|title=A Ritrovar Bellezza, le canzoni degli anni Sessanta secondo Diodato|website=Radio Italia}}</ref> In 2014 he participated in the [[Sanremo Music Festival]] and won the [[MTV Italian Music Awards]] for Best New Generation, The Deezer Band Of The Year Award and the Fabrizio de Andr\u00e9 Award.<ref>Big Time http://www.bigtimeweb.it/diodato</ref> He won the [[Sanremo Music Festival 2020]] with the song \"[[Fai rumore]]\" and will also represent [[Italy in the Eurovision Song Contest 2020|Italy]] at the [[Eurovision Song Contest 2020]].<ref>{{Cite web|title=Sanremo 2020: Ecco chi sono i 22 Big in gara della 70esima edizione del Festival|url=https://www.comingsoon.it/tv/anticipazioni/sanremo-2020-ecco-chi-sono-i-22-big-in-gara-della-70esima-edizione-del/n98831/|website=Coming Soon|date=31 December 2019|access-date=5 February 2020}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|title=Italy: Diodato wins Sanremo 2020!|url=https://eurovision.tv/story/italian-national-selection-sanremo-2020|website=Eurovision.tv|date=9 February 2020|access-date=9 February 2020}}</ref>\n\n==Discography==\n===Albums===\n{| class=\"wikitable plainrowheaders\" style=\"text-align:center;\"